{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 12:48:05.664512", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission details\n- Anomaly detected: true\n- Faulty devices: controller\n- Root cause: sdn_controller_crash\n\nRationale\n- All OVS switches report fail_mode=secure with zero flows and “Connection refused” to 20.0.0.100:6633.\n- IP reachability to the controller host is OK, isolating the issue to the controller’s OpenFlow service not accepting connections.\n- With the controller session down and fail_mode=secure, switches drop all data-plane traffic, leading to complete outage.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1552, "output_tokens": 114, "total_tokens": 1666, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1408}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
